Not all of the statements are true of all three sounds. Here are the correct statements:
They are voiced
They are approximants
They are consonants
The following statements are not true of all three sounds:
They are trills (Only [r] and [ʀ] are trills, [ʙ] is a bilabial approximant)
They are not used in human languages (All three sounds are used in human languages, although their frequency of occurrence may vary depending on the language)
They are palatal (Only [ʀ] is palatal, [r] is a postalveolar approximant and [ʙ] is a bilabial approximant)
